The paper discusses a formal model for representing contradictory information in textual sources, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of natural language processing and the discussion of contextuality in physics suggest that cs.AI and cs.CL are likely categories. The use of mathematical constructs such as lattices and sheaves suggests that cs.LO and cs.DS are also possible categories. Finally, the discussion of data fusion and topological data analysis suggests that cs.IT is a possible category as well.
